{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.35",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 35,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 35",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 35 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.35.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:1",
      "text": "And Elihu said:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.35.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:2",
      "text": "“Do you think this to be just? Do you say, ‘It is my right before God,’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.35.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:3",
      "text": "that you ask, ‘What advantage have I? How am I better off than if I had sinned?’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.35.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:4",
      "text": "I will answer you and your friends with you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.35.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:5",
      "text": "Look at the heavens, and see; and behold the clouds, which are higher than you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.35.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:6",
      "text": "If you have sinned, what do you accomplish against him? And if your transgressions are multiplied, what do you do to him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.35.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:7",
      "text": "If you are righteous, what do you give to him; or what does he receive from your hand?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.35.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:8",
      "text": "Your wickedness concerns a man like yourself, and your righteousness a son of man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.35.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:9",
      "text": "“Because of the multitude of oppressions people cry out; they call for help because of the arm of the mighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.35.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:10",
      "text": "But none says, ‘Where is God my Maker, who gives songs in the night,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.35.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:11",
      "text": "who teaches us more than the beasts of the earth, and makes us wiser than the birds of the air?’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.35.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:12",
      "text": "There they cry out, but he does not answer, because of the pride of evil men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.35.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:13",
      "text": "Surely God does not hear an empty cry, nor does the Almighty regard it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.35.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:14",
      "text": "How much less when you say that you do not see him, that the case is before him, and you are waiting for him!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.35.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:15",
      "text": "And now, because his anger does not punish, and he does not greatly heed transgression,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.35.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:16",
      "text": "Job opens his mouth in empty talk, he multiplies words without knowledge.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
